Content: Answer ALL questions.1 Snails can respond to a variety of stimuli, including touch. When a snail experiencesan unfamiliar stimulus, it will withdraw into its shell.After repeated exposure to the same stimulus, the snail will stop responding to thestimulus. This behaviour is called habituation.A Snail - Magnification x 2(a) Describe how you could investigate the habituation of a snail to a stimulus.UA ASA AP42 9 2 5 A 0 2 1 6

(b) (i) State two variables, other than the stimulus, which could affect theinvestigation.(ii) Choose one of these variables. Suggest how this variable could be controlled.Describe the effect the variable could have on the results if it is not controlled.3UA AAA Turn overP42 9 2 5 A 0 3 1 #6
(c) Suggest how calcium ions are involved in habituation in snails.(Total for Question 1 = 13 marks)P42 9 2 5 A 0 4 1 6

For each student he measured the FEV.three times.
